# KOVEGAS VISUAL DESIGN SYSTEM

You are designing a premium customer-facing travel website for Kovegas.com, operated by Las Vegas Mania Tour.

The website sells Las Vegas, Grand Canyon, Antelope Canyon, Zion, Bryce Canyon, and Southwest USA tours.

The interface must feel premium, trustworthy, modern, visually rich, and easy to book.

Do not create a generic SaaS dashboard design.

Do not create an overly playful travel blog design.

The visual direction should combine:

- Premium travel editorial design
- Modern hospitality website
- Clean Apple-inspired spacing
- High-quality destination photography
- Strong booking conversion UX
- Subtle Las Vegas personality

--------------------------------------------------
BRAND PERSONALITY
--------------------------------------------------

The brand must communicate:

- Professional local tour operator
- Safe and reliable
- Experienced local guides
- Premium but approachable
- Small-group expertise
- Clear and transparent pricing
- Multilingual customer service

Avoid:

- Cheap coupon website styling
- Excessive gradients
- Neon colors across the entire page
- Oversized rounded cards everywhere
- Excessive glassmorphism
- Excessive animations
- Generic AI-generated layouts
- Dashboard-like UI
- Too many different card designs
- Dense walls of text

--------------------------------------------------
DESIGN TOKENS
--------------------------------------------------

Use semantic design tokens instead of arbitrary color values.

Create and consistently use:

--background
--foreground
--card
--card-foreground
--muted
--muted-foreground
--primary
--primary-foreground
--secondary
--secondary-foreground
--accent
--accent-foreground
--border
--input
--ring
--success
--warning
--danger

Primary brand direction:

- Deep navy or near-black for trust and premium appearance
- Warm desert sand for neutral backgrounds
- Sunset orange or coral as the booking accent
- White and soft gray for clarity
- Green only for confirmation, availability, and trust indicators

Do not introduce new colors unless they are added to the global theme tokens.

--------------------------------------------------
TYPOGRAPHY
--------------------------------------------------

Use next/font.

Use one modern sans-serif font family for the primary UI.

Recommended direction:

- Inter
- Geist
- Manrope
- Plus Jakarta Sans

Use a display font only when it is subtle and limited to editorial headings.

Typography hierarchy:

Display:
text-4xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl
font-semibold or font-bold
tracking-tight
leading-[1.05]

Page title:
text-3xl md:text-5xl
font-semibold
tracking-tight

Section title:
text-2xl md:text-4xl
font-semibold
tracking-tight

Card title:
text-lg md:text-xl
font-semibold

Body:
text-base md:text-lg
leading-7
text-muted-foreground

Small labels:
text-xs or text-sm
font-medium
tracking-wide

Do not use more than three font weights on one page.

Avoid unnecessary uppercase text.

--------------------------------------------------
LAYOUT
--------------------------------------------------

All customer-facing pages must use a consistent container.

Use:

max-w-7xl
mx-auto
px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8

Standard section spacing:

py-16 md:py-24 lg:py-28

Compact sections:

py-10 md:py-16

Hero sections may use:

min-h-[70vh]
or
py-20 md:py-28 lg:py-36

Use generous whitespace.

Do not place every section inside a bordered card.

Alternate between:

- White background
- Soft neutral background
- Full-width photography
- Dark premium highlight section

Use asymmetrical editorial layouts when appropriate.

--------------------------------------------------
BORDER RADIUS
--------------------------------------------------

Use a controlled radius system.

- Buttons: rounded-lg or rounded-xl
- Inputs: rounded-lg
- Standard cards: rounded-xl
- Feature image cards: rounded-2xl
- Large editorial sections: rounded-2xl or rounded-3xl

Do not use rounded-3xl on every component.

Do not make all buttons pill-shaped.

Pill buttons should only be used for filters, tags, and compact status controls.

--------------------------------------------------
SHADOWS AND BORDERS
--------------------------------------------------

Use shadows sparingly.

Default cards:

border border-border/60
shadow-sm

Elevated interactive cards:

shadow-md
hover:shadow-lg

Do not use heavy dark shadows.

Prefer subtle borders, spacing, and background contrast over excessive shadows.

--------------------------------------------------
BUTTON SYSTEM
--------------------------------------------------

Use shared Button components.

Primary button:

- Strong brand accent
- High visual contrast
- Used for Book Now, Check Availability, Continue, and Reserve

Secondary button:

- Neutral or outlined
- Used for View Details and secondary actions

Ghost button:

- Navigation and low-priority actions only

Minimum button height:

h-11 on desktop
h-12 on mobile booking actions

Main booking buttons should be easy to tap and visually obvious.

Do not place more than two competing primary buttons in one viewport.

--------------------------------------------------
IMAGES
--------------------------------------------------

Travel photography is a primary part of the interface.

Use next/image for customer-facing images.

Every major page should use:

- One strong hero image
- Destination photography
- Real tour experience images when available
- Consistent aspect ratios
- Proper image overlays for text readability

Preferred aspect ratios:

- Hero: 16:9 or wide cinematic
- Tour cards: 4:3
- Gallery: mixed editorial grid
- Mobile cards: 4:3 or 3:2

Always provide meaningful alt text.

Do not stretch images.

Do not use low-quality placeholder gradients when destination images are available.

Use overlays carefully:

bg-gradient-to-t from-black/70 via-black/20 to-transparent

Do not place long paragraphs over images.

--------------------------------------------------
ICONS
--------------------------------------------------

Use lucide-react icons.

Do not use emojis as functional UI icons.

Use consistent sizing:

- 16px for small metadata
- 18–20px for controls
- 24px for feature icons

Icons should support the text, not replace important labels.

--------------------------------------------------
ANIMATION
--------------------------------------------------

Animations must be subtle and purposeful.

Allowed:

- Small fade and vertical entrance
- Card image zoom on hover
- Button micro-interactions
- Accordion transitions
- Sticky booking panel transitions
- Loading skeletons

Typical motion:

duration-200 or duration-300
ease-out

Do not animate every element.

Do not use large parallax effects that reduce performance.

Respect prefers-reduced-motion.

--------------------------------------------------
RESPONSIVE DESIGN
--------------------------------------------------

Design mobile-first.

Test at minimum:

- 375px
- 430px
- 768px
- 1024px
- 1440px

Mobile priorities:

- Tour name
- Price
- Review score
- Duration
- Pickup information
- Availability
- Booking button

On mobile:

- Use a sticky bottom booking bar
- Avoid wide tables
- Convert comparison tables into cards or accordions
- Keep key actions reachable with one hand
- Avoid excessive horizontal scrolling
- Keep tap targets at least 44px high

Do not simply shrink the desktop design.

--------------------------------------------------
ACCESSIBILITY
--------------------------------------------------

Use semantic HTML.

Every input must have a visible label.

Maintain sufficient color contrast.

All interactive elements must support keyboard navigation.

Use aria-label only when visible text is insufficient.

Do not communicate status through color alone.

Provide visible focus states.

--------------------------------------------------
COMPONENT CONSISTENCY
--------------------------------------------------

Before creating a new component:

1. Search the existing components.
2. Reuse an existing component when possible.
3. Extend an existing component through variants.
4. Only create a new component when no reusable component exists.

Shared components should include:

- Container
- Section
- SectionHeader
- Button
- TourCard
- TourGrid
- PriceDisplay
- ReviewSummary
- TrustBadge
- FeatureList
- IconText
- PickupInfo
- IncludedList
- ItineraryTimeline
- TourGallery
- BookingCard
- StickyBookingBar
- FAQSection
- RelatedTours
- EmptyState
- LoadingSkeleton

Do not duplicate component markup between pages.

--------------------------------------------------
QUALITY CHECK
--------------------------------------------------

Before completing any UI task, verify:

- Is the page visually consistent with the rest of the site?
- Does it look like a premium tour operator rather than a generic template?
- Is the booking action obvious?
- Is pricing easy to understand?
- Does mobile feel intentionally designed?
- Are repeated patterns componentized?
- Are all text and image states handled?
- Are hover, focus, loading, empty, and error states included?
- Are Supabase queries separated from presentation components?
- Are TypeScript errors avoided?
- Does the page preserve existing business logic?

Never declare the task complete until these checks are satisfied.